            <li><strong>Improved Comfort:</strong> Better humidity control, more even temperatures, and quieter operation.</li>
            <li><strong>Reliable Cooling:</strong> No more breakdowns on the hottest days of the year.</li>
            <li><strong>Warranty Protection:</strong> New equipment comes with manufacturer warranties for peace of mind.</li>
            <li><strong>Modern Features:</strong> Smart thermostat compatibility, variable-speed technology, and improved air filtration.</li>
            <li><strong>Environmentally Friendly:</strong> New systems use R-410A refrigerant, which doesn't deplete the ozone layer.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>AC Replacement Cost Factors</h2>
          <p>Several factors affect your replacement cost:</p>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>System Size:</strong> Larger homes require larger, more expensive systems.</li>
            <li><strong>Efficiency Rating:</strong> Higher SEER ratings cost more upfront but save money on energy bills.</li>
            <li><strong>System Type:</strong> Standard AC, heat pump, or ductless systems have different costs.</li>
            <li><strong>Ductwork Condition:</strong> If your ducts need repair or modification, this adds to the cost.</li>
            <li><strong>Electrical Requirements:</strong> Older homes may need electrical panel upgrades.</li>
            <li><strong>Brand & Features:</strong> Premium brands and advanced features affect pricing.</li>
          </ul>

